metadata.name: Block Dock #34
metadata.description:
Each output is generated by layering Blender renders.

Is it a space dock? Is it a ship dock? Where are they docking... and why?

'Block Dock' is a playful exploration of scale, form and color.

In live mode:
Click/tap the image to make a "Download image" button appear. Click this button to download a 1500x1500px PNG.

metadata.name: Alchemy #7
metadata.description:
Alchemy (or Maria Paritura) is a generative art project (p5js) based on Kandinsky's thoughts -Corcerning the Spiritual in Art-  about reducing artistic expression to his essentials. 

Inspired on a medieval painting of the Virgin pregnant with the sun. 
Shape has been removed and it has been synthesized into its primarial colours: blue, red and yellow. As soon as the figurative image is taken out, the symbolism comes out clearly. The union of heaven and earth reveals the Phylosopher's Stone. A sunrise where the Above finds the Below (As above so below, Esmerald Table). 

LVI (56) editions. 

Created by @mehno_art.

metadata.name: Chimalmat Relics #50
metadata.description:
'Chimalmat Relics' is a generative art project that pays homage to the great American civilizations (such as the Aztecs, the Mayans and the Incas).

Each piece of the project has 4 stages. 

The first is the expansion, the flourishing, the formation of the cities. In this stage each work begins to grow. The lines evoke the complexity of the cultures and how they progressed, occupying more land, becoming more intricate, complex, beautiful and elaborate. The circles represent the individuals of these cultures, they are large because they represent the greatness of these individuals. The squares represent the temples, so important to these societies.

The next stage is maturation, it is when lines begin to appear in the background that cover the entire piece and represent the acquired knowledge and wisdom of these cultures, their knowledge of nature, the stars, their art.

The third stage is decadence, we already know what happened to these civilizations, so this stage enters like a wave from the left that sweeps everything away, erases and blurs the work, the history. It represents the conquest.

The last stage represents history, memory, what survives today, what we can reconstruct, infer, yearn for those times, there is much that was lost, but the essence remains, it is still there. It allows us and obliges us in a certain way to contemplate and appreciate it.

-----

Press 'e' to export a PNG

-----

Artwork by @cristianrohr 2022.

Made with P5js and <3.

metadata.name: Perspective #81
metadata.description:
A few primitives and a lot of points.

Warning: This piece is GPU intensive, it may not render on lower end devices.

Keys
s: Take a screenshot
space: Pause/Play the animation.
r: Play a new animation
↑: Increase point alpha
↓: Decrease point alpha
→: Increase point density
←: Decrease point density

URL Params
w: Width of the canvas - (ex, w=1024) - [0-2048]
h: Height of the canvas - (ex, h=1024) - [0-2048]
a: To set the alpha for the points - [0.0-1.0]
p: To set the total number of points to draw (in millions) [1-8]
s: Make the visual static - (ex, s=1)

metadata.name: glory hole$ #178
metadata.description:
our consciousness as humans can be distilled into a crudely fashioned hole at an abandoned dave & busters and the meditative state that is endured while sitting on a neglected toilet praying for the sound of disrupted waters. glory holes embody anonymity and pleasure for pleasure's sake. they are creations that cannot be destroyed, as they exist in the memories of anyone who uses or witnesses. many speculate that the carving of the hole is the purest form of human ingenuity and the desire to explore the unknown. formerly limited to the physical space. these glory holes transcend space and time. and exist in that same unknown that tempts us all. legalize ground beef. create nothing. consume everything.

HUGE thank you to @PureSpider for the layered PNG template, this dream would not have been realized without you friend.

metadata.name: blinksquare 2022 #47
metadata.description:
From the pixel-lab vault - evolved from 'blinksquare' (2008) 
---------------------------------------------------------------------
Mouse-click switches between:
- screen scaled image
- The large image (for printing)

Right-click: Save/Copy the image

A custom created 'soft' pixel 2D/3D engine,
written in vanilla JavaScript some more info in the source-code
- The work will refresh and restart after some time -
-------------------------------------------------

I created 'blinksquare' back in 2008 in Secondlife,
it was like a kinetic 3D sculpture; that would change over time.

I wanted to do a 2022 remake; and while working on it; it evolved a bit.
Also inspired by writing and ancient Hieroglyphs from around the world 


xxx Amsterdam chillout


For the love of Art, hugging someone you love, and filling that RGB-and Z buffer  ^__^

metadata.name: Roasting Humans #7
metadata.description:
========
Concept
========
Humanists live in a world built on human bones.
The fuel of humanism is human sacrifices.

Eating flesh is natural for animals.
But humans are eating  life energy, results of work, time  of other humans.

Social status is in general about how many humans you personally can devour.
Personal freedom in general about how not to be eaten by other humans.

Sweet promises, beautiful concepts, inspiring ideas - basically ways to put  the victim on the skewer.

Humanism today is an attempt to inject anesthesia into the basic process of eating others.
Slavery must be gentle and invisible.
Weapons must be lethal and not cause suffering.
People should be polite and tolerant.
You must not feel that your blood is being sucked out.

If the victim does not feel the pain and does not scream: is the victim a plant? Is predator a vegan?

Is it better to you feel pain or inject anesthesia?
Anesthesia today is not only drugs, but entertainment.

Are you enjoy of eating others?
So check if you are on a skewer and how roasted you are.

==============
Technical Details
==============
Mangal size calculating depending on humans amount (min=5; max=111) and skewer parameters.

You can roast the bodies from different sides using the control buttons.
The bodies are divided into sectors that absorb thermal energy differently depending on the angle of rotation.
The amount of absorbed energy determines the degree of roasting.
The camera is focused on the active skewer, to select another one, press the button or select from the list.

Press the left mouse button to rotate the point of view.
Hold down the right mouse button to move the point of view.
